85.title: Diplomatic Relations
85.plot: Part one of two. - Visitors to Nashville TN from Russia and Poland Have more fun in the Car than in the Bar. Attempting to sing Caraoke that's Karaoke to go.

86.title: Diplomatic Relations 2
86.plot: Visitors from Russia and Poland visit Nashville TN and perform Karaoke Poorly on board with James on the previous episode so James Turns it on as the Lead Caraoke Singer of "Pour Some Sugar on me" and the Party was on..

imdb.plot outline: An Original Concept by James Hammond of Creation Multimedia. As a Rideshare Driver to Customize the car to be a Honky Tonk on Wheels with lights and even Live Entertainment.. - - - Karaoke that means the Riders are the Stars of the Car. - with the Caraokemobile ready riders are treated to a similar concept of Cash Cab where the Car looks normal then with the flip of a switch it is converted to a Caraoke Stage. Hammond a Brand and Talent Manager has billed it as a way to audition Nashville's Next Star in his Car.
